                     <title xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc">Jāmiʻ al-qawānīn</title>
                     <title xml:lang="ar">جامع القوانين</title>
                     <note>Inside front cover: armorial bookplate of Gordon of Buthlaw. Inside back cover, printed slip, perhaps from a sale catalogue: Pand Nama of Saadi : Jamiu'l-Kawanin, being a Collection of Forms of Letter-writing &amp;c. and another Work on Epistolary Correspondence. I vol. loose. Headings and punctuation in red. Numerous glosses in red in earlier part.</note>
                     <incipit>Sitayish u niyayish mar khuday-ra (sic, for ahadi-ra)</incipit>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>Storey, iii, pp. 313-5.</bibl>
                        <bibl>Rieu, i, pp. 414-5.</bibl>
                        <bibl>Ethe No 2097.</bibl>
                        <bibl>General Gordon's bequest of books and Turkish, Perian and Arabic manuscripts is mentioned, without details in the donations register under November 6 1841. The bequest is mentioned in J.R.A.S., vii, 1843, Annual Report, p. x, and the manuscripts are briefly listed in the Proceedings, pp. xxx-xxxi. According to Morley's handwritten catalogue the manuscript came from Major David Price, but this is evidently a mistake; the manuscript is listed in J.R.A.S. vii.</bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian.</textLang>
                  </msItem>
